title: Bug 109350 - Output parameter should display in data set dialog.
description: When calling a stored procedure from an Oracle database, the query result is stored in an output parameter as an object. However, while on the query result page, no data is returned. The expected behavior is that the output parameter should display in the edit data set dialog.
OB: While on the query result page, there is no data returned.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
SR:
To reproduce this issue:
1. Call the stored procedure from an Oracle database.
2. Check the query result page for the absence of data.
3. Open the edit data set dialog and verify that the output parameter is not displayed.
